                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="17833125" author="JIRAUSER297279" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 10:45:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi&#65281;Can this kind of text that cannot be displayed be displayed using lastResortFont?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833158" author="tilman" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 12:04:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The file has a font named &quot;element&quot; with no glyphs. However the maxp table claims there is 1 glyph.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833159" author="tilman" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 12:05:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this rendering complete?&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13067801/13067801_screenshot-1.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833163" author="JIRAUSER297279" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 12:12:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, as long as the text can be displayed and not lost, it will be fine. After all, there is a problem with the embedded fonts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833197" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 13:15:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1916746 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1916746&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1916746&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5794&quot; title=&quot;The content of the specified font is lost&#65292;Google Chrome can display it&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5794&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5794&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: detect empty font; remove super&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833198" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 13:16:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1916747 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/3.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1916747&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1916747&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5794&quot; title=&quot;The content of the specified font is lost&#65292;Google Chrome can display it&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5794&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5794&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: detect empty font; remove super&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833199" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 13:17:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1916748 from Tilman Hausherr in branch &apos;pdfbox/branches/2.0&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1916748&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1916748&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5794&quot; title=&quot;The content of the specified font is lost&#65292;Google Chrome can display it&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-5794&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-5794&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: detect empty font&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17833210" author="tilman" created="Tue, 2 Apr 2024 14:02:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report. The modified code looks at the &quot;loca&quot; table and throws an exception if there is only one glyph that is empty. PDFBox will then use a replacement font, here &quot;Using fallback font ArialMT for FAAACE+element&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
